        <num>CCRP 327</num>
        <heading>327.  Those who may not be sureties</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 327.  Those who may not be sureties
A person shall not be released on bail for which an attorney at law, a judge, or
ministerial officer of a court becomes a surety or provides money or property for bail; but the
invalidity of such bail shall not be a defense to an action to forfeit and enforce the bail.</p>
        </content>
